The paper deals with the Rural Postman Problem, which is a graph theory problem involving finding a closed walk of minimum total weight containing all edges of a given subset. This problem is related to several subfields of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), graph theory (cs.GT), computational complexity (cs.CC), and robotics (cs.RO). The paper's focus on parameterized complexity and kernelization suggests that cs.DS, cs.DM, and cs.CC are the most likely categories, while the experimental evaluation and real-world applications suggest that cs.GT and cs.RO are also relevant.
